      <scopecontent id="aspace_a29c48f4b234ecbd1ccc572daedde6f0">
         <head>Content Description</head>
         <p>Tom Ferguson (1943-2006), Yale School of Medicine class of 1977, was a medical doctor, educator, and author. Ferguson was an early advocate for patient empowerment, urging patients to educate themselves, to assume control of their own health care, and to use the Internet as a way of accomplishing those goals. The bulk of the collection consists of publications written and/or edited by Ferguson which includes issues of <title>
               <part>Medical Self Care</part>
            </title> from 1970-1990; <title>
               <part>Whole Earth</part>
            </title> catalogs and supplements; and multiple books. The collection also includes photographs; media (a U-matic tape, VHS tapes, cassette tapes, DVDs); materials from talks, workshops, interviews, and presentations; clippings; and a copy of Ferguson's curriculum vitae.</p>
      </scopecontent>
